"title": "1450: signs, kinds of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1450: signs, kinds of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Signs are miraculous events, supernatural phenomena or everyday things that are given a special significance. The term is used in John's Gospel to describe the miracles of Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>Miraculous signs</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:12\">2CO 12:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod10:1\">EXO 10:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:43\">PSA 78:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:27\">PSA 105:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:24\">MAT 24:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:22\">MRK 13:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:17\">MRK 16:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:43\">ACT 2:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:19\">ROM 15:19</a></p>\n<h2>The signs of Jesus Christ in John's Gospel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:11\">JHN 2:11</a></strong> <em>John refers to the miracles of Jesus Christ as “signs” in order to bring out the significance of these deeds.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:26\">JHN 6:26</a> <em>Jesus Christ, the bread of life</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:16\">JHN 9:16</a> <em>Jesus Christ, the light of the world</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:47\">JHN 11:47</a> <em>Jesus Christ, the resurrection and the life</em></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ refers to Jonah as a sign</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:39-Matt12:41\">MAT 12:39–12:41</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:29-Luke11:32\">LUK 11:29–11:32</a></p>\n<h2>Prophetic signs</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:12\">EXO 3:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:7-1Sam10:9\">1SA 10:7–10:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs13:1-1Kgs13:5\">1KI 13:1–13:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:29\">2KI 19:29</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:30\">ISA 37:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:14-Isa7:17\">ISA 7:14–7:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:18\">ISA 8:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:19-Isa19:20\">ISA 19:19–19:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:12\">LUK 2:12</a></p>\n<h2>Signs of protection</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:13\">EXO 12:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:23\">EXO 12:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:12-Josh2:13\">JOS 2:12–2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:17-Josh2:21\">JOS 2:17–2:21</a></p>\n<h2>Signs given to guarantee promises</h2>\n<h3>The rainbow</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:12\">GEN 9:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:13-Gen9:17\">GEN 9:13–9:17</a></p>\n<h3>Circumcision</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:10-Gen17:11\">GEN 17:10–17:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:12-Gen17:14\">GEN 17:12–17:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:11\">ROM 4:11</a></p>\n<h2>Signs serve as reminders of past blessings</h2>\n<h3>Monuments</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh4:4-Josh4:7\">JOS 4:4–4:7</a></p>\n<h3>Religious observances</h3>\n<p>Passover:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:9\">EXO 13:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:16\">EXO 13:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:12-Exod31:17\">EXO 31:12–31:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:12\">EZK 20:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:20\">EZK 20:20</a></p>\n<h2>Signs associated with the birth of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>The virgin birth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:14\">ISA 7:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:22-Matt1:23\">MAT 1:22–1:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:34-Luke1:36\">LUK 1:34–1:36</a></p>\n<h3>The birthplace</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:12\">LUK 2:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:7\">LUK 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:16\">LUK 2:16</a></p>\n<h3>The star</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:1-Matt2:2\">MAT 2:1–2:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:9-Matt2:10\">MAT 2:9–2:10</a></p>\n<h2>Signs associated with the death of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Darkness at midday</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:45\">MAT 27:45</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:33\">MRK 15:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:44-Luke23:45\">LUK 23:44–23:45</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:9\">AMO 8:9</a></p>\n<h3>The curtain of the temple torn in two</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:51\">MAT 27:51</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:38\">MRK 15:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:45\">LUK 23:45</a></p>\n<h3>The dead came back to life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:51-Matt27:53\">MAT 27:51–27:53</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Signs associated with the coming of the Holy Spirit</h2>\n<h3>The sound like a violent wind</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:2\">ACT 2:2</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Tongues of fire</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:3\">ACT 2:3</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Speaking in other languages</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:4\">ACT 2:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:5-Acts2:11\">ACT 2:5–2:11</a></p>\n<h2>Signs associated with the second coming of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>General signs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:3-Matt24:8\">MAT 24:3–24:8</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:4-Mark13:8\">MRK 13:4–13:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:7-Luke21:11\">LUK 21:7–21:11</a></p>\n<h3>Signs preceding the second coming</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:9-Matt24:24\">MAT 24:9–24:24</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:9-Mark13:22\">MRK 13:9–13:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:12-Luke21:24\">LUK 21:12–21:24</a></p>\n<h3>Signs simultaneous with the second coming</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:27-Matt24:31\">MAT 24:27–24:31</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:24-Mark13:27\">MRK 13:24–13:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:25-Luke21:27\">LUK 21:25–21:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:24\">LUK 17:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:19-Acts2:20\">ACT 2:19–2:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:30-Joel2:31\">JOL 2:30–2:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:12-2Pet3:13\">2PE 3:12–3:13</a></p>\n<h2>False signs</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut13:1-Deut13:3\">DEU 13:1–13:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:25\">ISA 44:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:24\">MAT 24:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:22\">MRK 13:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:9\">2TH 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:11-Rev13:14\">REV 13:11–13:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:14\">REV 16:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:20\">REV 19:20</a></p>",
